    "b-20-block-vocabulary-seven-ops-11": {
      "id": "b-20-block-vocabulary-seven-ops-11",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Everything is an op. The kernel ("
        },
        {
          "insert": "doc-ops.ts",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ") speaks "
        },
        {
          "insert": "seven ops",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ": six generic structural/text ops — "
        },
        {
          "insert": "insertBlock",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", "
        },
        {
          "insert": "updateBlock",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", "
        },
        {
          "insert": "deleteBlock",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", "
        },
        {
          "insert": "moveBlock",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", "
        },
        {
          "insert": "splitBlock",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", "
        },
        {
          "insert": "mergeBlocks",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " — plus "
        },
        {
          "insert": "blockAction",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", the typed-action bridge. Ops post to "
        },
        {
          "insert": "POST /api/ops",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " with an "
        },
        {
          "insert": "expected_hash",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " precondition (409 on a stale hash, 423 while another editor holds the draft lock). Every applied op returns "
        },
        {
          "insert": "exact inverse ops",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", stored as undo units keyed by patch id and replayed through "
        },
        {
          "insert": "POST /api/undo",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-20-block-vocabulary-write-path-mermaid-12": {
      "id": "b-20-block-vocabulary-write-path-mermaid-12",
      "type": "mermaid",
      "props": {
        "caption": "Typed actions ride the same kernel: blockAction resolves to an updateBlock props patch, so undo comes free.",
        "title": "The one write path"
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "flowchart LR\n  agent[\"agent / editor\"] -->|\"POST /api/ops + expected_hash\"| kernel[\"applyOps kernel\"]\n  kernel -->|\"exact inverse ops\"| undo[\"undo stack\"]\n  kernel -->|\"doc + fresh hash\"| agent\n  kernel -->|\"SSE change event\"| watchers[\"GET /api/events\"]"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-20-block-vocabulary-typed-actions-intro-13": {
      "id": "b-20-block-vocabulary-typed-actions-intro-13",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Object types with structured props carry "
        },
        {
          "insert": "typed actions",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " ("
        },
        {
          "insert": "block-actions.ts",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ") instead of hand-edited props JSON: a "
        },
        {
          "insert": "blockAction",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " op names an action ("
        },
        {
          "insert": "\"<blockType>.<verb>\"",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "), the action validates its own params and returns a shallow-merge props patch, and the kernel executes that patch through the existing "
        },
        {
          "insert": "updateBlock",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " path — same merge semantics, same undo inverse. There are 13 actions across four types: code (2), structured-table (5), file-tree (3), interaction-surface (3). "
        },
        {
          "insert": "GET /api/blocks",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " is the discovery endpoint: it returns "
        },
        {
          "insert": "{ schemaVersion, genericOps, blockTypes }",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " with each type's category and actions, so agents learn how to edit each block type instead of reverse-engineering props. The four surfaces below mirror that registry, one per object type:"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
